-- BMW's South African Financial Services Unit Sells $336 Million of Bonds
-- Vernon Wessels
-- 2010-06-21T08:12:39Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-21/bmw-s-south-african-financial-services-unit-sells-336-million-of-bonds.html

          
          
              Bayerische Motoren Werke AG’s South
African financial services unit sold 2.5 billion rand of bonds,
the largest issue in the country since October 2008, Absa
Capital, which arranged the sale, said.  
 The bonds, guaranteed by the German carmaker, mature over
one, two and three years, Johannesburg-based Absa Capital, a
unit of Barclays Plc’s Absa Group Ltd., said in an e-mailed
statement today. The offer was 2.1 times oversubscribed, it
said.  
          
          


  


        